messages.message:
Hi all, do we know which agent/client is making request like the following that tries to ListDir a folder named "Background" that doesn't exist in many cases?
```2022/07/21 04:27:18 ERROR fileservice/handler/file.go:269 -- [ERROR][list_dir] Username: {user_name}, Path: system/global/fs/Instabase Drive/System/Desktop/Background, Err: rpc error: code = NotFound desc = Folder System/Desktop/Background does not exist: <nil>, Time: 356ms, Size: 0Bytes```
I don't think the user_name is telling us what's the mechanism behind and I've seen this error from time to time. It is not affecting anything as far as I know, but mostly just curious about what this is about.

This must be launcher. Whenever anyone loads the Instabase desktop, it first checks if a different “Background” wallpaper image exists at that location, if it does, it uses it. If it doesn’t exist, it uses the default yosemite one we see.
@Jessica I remember us discussing this a while ago, but I wasn’t sure that we actually implemented the change though
Ah got it, thanks for clarifying. :+1:
